      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis model adequacy supported by published literature survey",
      "description": "A comprehensive review of peer-reviewed publications on CFD-based hemolysis prediction in centrifugal blood pumps was conducted. Seventeen studies were identified that employed the power-law hemolysis model under comparable shear-stress and exposure-time regimes. The review confirms that the model constants used in this assessment fall within the range reported in the literature and that relative hemolysis index predictions are consistent with published numerical benchmarks. This evidence is presented as the primary support for the hemolysis model validation requirement.",
